    <item>
      <title>Local Government Overlap</title>
      <link>https://www.cgoodman.com/blog/archives/2019/09/23/local-government-overlap/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Sep 2019 11:49:02 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.cgoodman.com/blog/archives/2019/09/23/local-government-overlap/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;files/misc/ca-cog-17.png&#34;
         alt=&#34;Western states have the highest levels of local government overlap&#34;/&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Local government overlap is calculated similar to &lt;a href=&#34;https://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-5907.2008.00344.x&#34;&gt;Berry (2008)&lt;/a&gt; by taking the ratio of all special districts, school districts, and overlapping townships to municipalities and non-overlapping townships in a county. Unlike Berry, this includes all forms of overlapping jurisdictions rather than just those with taxing power.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
